-- Petronas New LNG Train in Malaysia Sets Up Engineers’ Contest
-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 2012-02-23T04:32:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/petronas-new-lng-train-in-malaysia-sets-up-engineers-contest.html
Petroliam Nasional Bhd (PET) . is asking
engineers to compete for a contract to build a new liquefied
natural gas train in  Malaysia .  JGC Corp. (1963)  will compete for the project against a joint
partnership of  Chiyoda Corp. (6366)  and  Saipem SpA (SPM) , Malaysia’s state
oil company said today in an e-mailed statement. Petronas plans
to build a ninth train at its  LNG complex in Bintulu, Sarawak ,
increasing output capacity by 3.6 metric million tons a year,
it said.  The project is scheduled to start in the fourth quarter of
2015. The new train will require as much as 850 million cubic 
feeta day of natural gas coming from offshore fields near 
Sarawak, the company said.  Petronas plans to award the contract, including 
engineering,construction and commissioning, in December this 
year. The complex at Bintulu currently has eight trains capable 
of producing 24 million tons a year of LNG, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
